A widow from Magombe village, Siaya county, commited suicide upon discovering she had been sharing a man with her daughter. According to villagers, the woman could not handle the information she had been sharing a man with her secondary school daughter. The incident had caused concern among the woman’s in-laws, who were brainstorming on how to cleanse her and her daughter. However, villagers woke up on Thursday morning to find the woman’s body dangling from a mango tree in her compound. Chief Wilberforce Oyucho said investigations are underway. The woman’s body has been moved to Madiany Subcounty Hospital mortuary. Elsewhere in Bondo, a 33-year-old man is being held at Bondo police station after he was allegedly caught with a neighbour’s wife at Nyapiedho trading centre The man is said to have been caught red-handed.  